cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on abstractive summarization using neural techniques. This is the most likely category for this paper. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning techniques to develop an abstractive summarization model, which falls under the umbrella of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses various attention mechanisms and optimization techniques to improve the performance of the abstractive summarization model, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with summarization of text, which is a subfield of information retrieval. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural techniques to develop an abstractive summarization model, which falls under the category of neural computing.
